.TH SHAPE2SVG 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
shape2svg \- export named polygons of an ESRI shapefile as SVG paths
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shape2svg
.RI [ options ]
.I shapename
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shape2svg
reads an ESRI shapefile and writes one file per distinct value of the
chosen attribute. Each output file contains the polygon geometry in
SVG path data form, as consumed by the
.B qdtext
text\(hygeneration toolchain. The output is not a complete SVG document,
only a path; the round\(hytrip back to a shapefile is provided by
.BR svg2shape (1).
.PP
The polygons present in a shape can be inspected with
.BR shape2xml (1).
For example,
.PP
.RS 4
shape2xml regions | grep '<shape'
.RE
.PP
will list the named features. Then
.PP
.RS 4
shape2svg \-f NAME regions
.RE
.PP
extracts each named polygon to its own
.IR NAME .svg
file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-f " name"
Attribute used to choose output filenames (default
.BR NAME ).
The attribute must be of string type.
.TP
.BI \-d " dir"
Output directory (default
.BR . ).
.TP
.B \-h
Print help.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR svg2shape (1),
.BR shape2xml (1),
.BR shape2ps (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
